class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 20, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gfe1665702721892.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gfe1665702721892.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gfe1665702721892.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gfe1665702721892\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the default keyboard and display table name.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__topic_d140105e1_d140106e1_d140107e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__p_d140108e1_d140109e1_d140110e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_TERM</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <var class=\"keyword varname\">TranslationTableName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__section_gx4_l3q_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d512128e65\"> Defaults </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16646e1_d16647e1_d16648e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Assignment file: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> client assignment files </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Section: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> [SETTINGS] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__section_mjw_q3q_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d512128e111\"> Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__p_d140117e1_d140118e1_d140119e1\">If Uniface cannot determine what kind of translation\n        table to use, or if the defined table cannot be found, it uses the default terminal tables\n        specified by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_TERM</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__p_d140120e1_d140121e1_d140122e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_TERM</span> sets the (combined) default keyboard and display table name\n        for the application. If you have not used <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$KEYBOARD</span> and\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DISPLAY</span> to define the keyboard and display in use, and if the UKEYB\n        and UDISP system variables are not defined, the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_TERM</span> setting is\n        used when the application starts.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__p_d140123e1_d140124e1_d140125e1\">If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_TERM</span> has not been set\n        in an assignment file, Uniface uses an appropriate default. The choice of a default table is\n        determined by the GUI being used.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Default values for $DISPLAY and $KEYBOARD</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__1\"> GUI in use </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__2\"> $GUI Assignment Setting </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__3\"> Default value </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__1\"> Character mode </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__2\"> $CHR </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__3\"> USYSTERM </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__1\"> Microsoft Windows </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__2\"> $MSW </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"gfe1665702721892__table_d16649e1_d16650e1_d16651e1__entry__3\"> MSWIN3 </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__p_d140126e1_d140127e1_d140128e1\">If <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_TERM</span> is not assigned\n        and the system returns a terminal type of ‘unknown’, Uniface opts for the USYSTERM by\n        default. USYSTERM is a very basic device driver designed to work in as many environments as\n        possible, on the basis of managing the ‘lowest common denominator’ of requirements. It is\n        always better to specify the exact keyboard and display device translation tables with\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$KEYBOARD</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DISPLAY</span> or with the UKEYB and UDISP\n        system variables.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__section_sfg_x3q_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle exampletitle\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__p_d140129e1_d140130e1_d140131e1\">Example: $DEFAULT_TERM </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__p_d140132e1_d140133e1_d140134e1\">Setting <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEFAULT_TERM</span> to ‘VT’ is a\n        good way of covering almost all VT-series terminals and clones.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"gfe1665702721892__pre_nns_bjq_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$DEFAULT_TERM = VT</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/icm1665703229996.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$KEYBOARD</a><p>Specify a translation table for input characters.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zkc1665703224453.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$DISPLAY</a><p>Specify a translation table for display in character-based user interface (CHUI).</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ovw1665703227836.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$GUI</a><p>Specify the GUI driver, which determines whether the application will run in Windows or character mode.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527829\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527829\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$DEFAULT_TERM Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Set the default keyboard and display table name. $DEFAULT_TERM { = } TranslationTableName Defaults Assignment file: client assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: None Description If Uniface cannot determine what kind of translation table to use, or if the defined table cannot be found, it uses the default terminal tables specified by $DEFAULT_TERM . $DEFAULT_TERM sets the (combined) default keyboard and display table name for the application. If you have not used $KEYBOARD and $DISPLAY to define the keyboard and display in use, and if the UKEYB and UDISP system variables are not defined, the $DEFAULT_TERM setting is used when the application starts. If $DEFAULT_TERM has not been set in an assignment file, Uniface uses an appropriate default. The choice of a default table is determined by the GUI being used. Table 1. Default values for $DISPLAY and $KEYBOARD GUI in use $GUI Assignment Setting Default value Character mode $CHR USYSTERM Microsoft Windows $MSW MSWIN3 If $DEFAULT_TERM is not assigned and the system returns a terminal type of ‘unknown’, Uniface opts for the USYSTERM by default. USYSTERM is a very basic device driver designed to work in as many environments as possible, on the basis of managing the ‘lowest common denominator’ of requirements. It is always better to specify the exact keyboard and display device translation tables with $KEYBOARD and $DISPLAY or with the UKEYB and UDISP system variables. Example: $DEFAULT_TERM Setting $DEFAULT_TERM to ‘VT’ is a good way of covering almost all VT-series terminals and clones. $DEFAULT_TERM = VT Copy Related Links $KEYBOARD Specify a translation table for input characters. $DISPLAY Specify a translation table for display in character-based user interface (CHUI). $GUI Specify the GUI driver, which determines whether the application will run in Windows or character mode. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}